{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 09:31:14.816332", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary\\n- Anomaly detected: East–west connectivity between hosts is broken toward pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2). The data center fabric control plane (EBGP across leaves, spines, super-spine) is healthy and properly exchanging routes.\\n- Fault localization: Edge segment between leaf_router_0_1 and host pc_0_1. Specifically, pc_0_1’s NIC is down, preventing L2 adjacency and ARP resolution.\\n- Root cause: pc_0_1 eth0 is administratively/operationally DOWN and has no default route; leaf_router_0_1 cannot resolve ARP for 10.0.1.2 (INCOMPLETE), leading to “Destination Host Unreachable” for traffic destined to pc_0_1.\\n\\nEvidence and Findings\\n\\nReachability tests\\n- pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1:\\n  - Result: 100% loss; “From 172.16.0.7 Destination Host Unreachable”\\n  - Interpretation: Leaf 0_1 (IP 172.16.0.7) received the traffic via the fabric but could not deliver to the host subnet 10.0.1.0/24.\\n- pc_0_1 -> pc_0_0:\\n  - Result: “ping: connect: Network is unreachable”\\n  - Interpretation: Local host routing/interface issue on pc_0_1.\\n\\nHost edge state\\n- pc_0_0:\\n  - eth0 UP, 10.0.0.2/24, default via 10.0.0.1 present.\\n- pc_0_1:\\n  - eth0 DOWN (ip addr shows state DOWN), IP 10.0.1.2/24 configured but no routes (empty routing table).\\n  - Consequence: Cannot send traffic (no default route) and cannot receive routed traffic (interface down prevents ARP replies).\\n\\nLeaf 0_1 (connected to pc_0_1)\\n- ARP/Neighbor:\\n  - ip neigh show dev eth2: “10.0.1.2 INCOMPLETE” (no ARP resolution).\\n  - Ping 10.0.1.2 from leaf_router_0_1: 100% loss.\\n- Routing table:\\n  - Connected 10.0.1.0/24 via eth2.\\n  - BGP-learned 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.6.\\n- Interpretation: Control-plane and upstream reachability are correct; L2 to host is failing.\\n\\nControl-plane health (BGP)\\n- All EBGP sessions established as expected:\\n  - Leaves (AS 65200, 65201) have established sessions with both spines and advertise their connected /24s; each reports receiving 1 prefix from each spine neighbor.\\n  - Spines (AS 65100, 65101) have established sessions with super-spine (AS 65000) and both leaves; each spine has both /24s via respective leaves.\\n  - Super-spine has established sessions to both spines and has both /24s in RIB.\\n- Route tables across fabric show both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 propagated correctly with next-hops toward the correct leaves.\\n- Conclusion: No control-plane anomalies detected in the Clos fabric.\\n\\nImpact assessment\\n- Traffic destined to or sourced from pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2) fails due to host edge issue.\\n- Fabric routing is unaffected and functioning normally; pc_0_0 and its leaf side appear healthy.\\n\\nRoot cause\\n- pc_0_1’s interface eth0 is down and the host has no default route. The down interface prevents ARP resolution on leaf_router_0_1 (ARP INCOMPLETE), causing “Destination Host Unreachable” for inbound traffic to 10.0.1.2 and “Network is unreachable” for outbound traffic from pc_0_1.\\n\\nNo remediation steps are provided per instructions., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='7ad8026a-f628-4566-9cca-c820643ef5ec'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
